                    </text>
                </otherAnnotation>
            </annotations>
            <attribute conformance="R"
                defaultValue="COCD_TP146076UK02#CarePlanComponent"
                fixedValue="COCD_TP146076UK02#CarePlanComponent"
                isMandatory="true" maximumMultiplicity="1"
                minimumMultiplicity="1" name="templateId" sortKey="0">
                <annotations>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>
                            <div>
                                <p>The fixed value of this attribute provides a unique identifier for the  template and the classname within that template.</p>
                                <p>The IdentifierExternal datatype flavour is used to carry this information as follows:</p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>The root attribute shall contain the OID "2.16.840.1.113883.2.1.3.2.4.18.2"</li>
                                    <li>The extension attribute shall contain the fixed value.</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </text>
                    </otherAnnotation>
                </annotations>
                <derivationSupplier attributeName="templateId"
                    className="Act" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
                <type name="II"/>
            </attribute>
            <attribute conformance="R" isMandatory="true"
                isStructural="true" maximumMultiplicity="1"
                minimumMultiplicity="1" name="classCode" sortKey="0">
                <annotations>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>
                            <div contenteditable="false" style="height: 100%; width: 100%">
                                <div contenteditable="false" style="height: 100%; width: 100%">
                                    <div>
                                    <p>The class code of the Care Plan component. </p>
                                    <p>The value of class code should be set according to the information and context of the coded entry information being carried in the Care Plan component class. </p>
                                    <p>The CodedOnly datatype flavour is used to carry this information as  follows:</p>
                                    <ul>
                                    <li>The <i>code</i> attribute will contain a value from the list of codes in the x_ActClassDocumentEntryAct vocabulary. </li>
                                    </ul>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </text>
                    </otherAnnotation>
                </annotations>
                <derivationSupplier attributeName="classCode"
                    className="Act" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
                <type name="CS"/>
                <supplierDomainSpecification codingStrength="CNE" domainName="x_ActClassDocumentEntryAct"/>
            </attribute>
            <attribute conformance="R" isMandatory="true"
                isStructural="true" maximumMultiplicity="1"
                minimumMultiplicity="1" name="moodCode" sortKey="0">
                <annotations>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>
                            <div contenteditable="false" style="height: 100%; width: 100%">
                                <div contenteditable="false" style="height: 100%; width: 100%">
                                    <div>
                                    <p>The mood code of the Care Plan component. </p>
                                    <p>The value of mood code should be set according to the information and context  of the coded entry information being carried                            in the Care Plan component class.                                                </p>
                                    <p>The CodedOnly datatype flavour is used to carry this information as  follows:</p>
                                    <ul>
                                    <li>The <i>code</i> attribute will contain a value from the list of codes in  the x_DocumentActMood vocabulary.                                                                                  </li>
                                    </ul>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </text>
                    </otherAnnotation>
                </annotations>
                <derivationSupplier attributeName="moodCode"
                    className="Act" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
                <type name="CS"/>
                <supplierDomainSpecification codingStrength="CNE" domainName="x_DocumentActMood"/>
            </attribute>
            <attribute conformance="R" isMandatory="true"
                maximumMultiplicity="1" minimumMultiplicity="1"
                name="id" sortKey="0">
                <annotations>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>
                            <div contenteditable="false" style="height: 100%; width: 100%">
                                <div contenteditable="false" style="height: 100%; width: 100%">
                                    <div>
                                    <p>This is a unique identifier for this instance of a Care Plan component.  </p>
                                    <p>The Identifier Global data type flavour is used to carry the  identifiers follows: </p>
                                    <ul>
                                    <li>The <em>root</em> attribute shall contain a DCE UUID.                                                     </li>
                                    </ul>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </text>
                    </otherAnnotation>
                </annotations>
                <derivationSupplier attributeName="id" className="Act" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
                <type name="II" typeSpecialisation="II.NPfIT.uuid.mandatory"/>
            </attribute>
            <attribute conformance="R" defaultValue="CPC"
                fixedValue="CPC" isMandatory="true"
                maximumMultiplicity="1" minimumMultiplicity="1"
                name="code" sortKey="0">
                <annotations>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>A code from the vocabulary shown indicating that this is a Care Plan Component.<br/>The Coded Value (CV) with CDA URL datatype/flavour shall be used to carry this information as follows:<br/>
                            <br/>
                            <ul>
                                <li>    The code attribute shall contain a code from the relevant vocabulary</li>
                                <li>    The codeSystem attribute shall contain the OID for the vocabulary</li>
                                <li>    The displayName attribute shall carry the description associated with the code</li>
                                <li>    The originalText element can be used to carry a reference element. This can link the coded item to the relevant text in the CDA section</li>
                            </ul>
                            <br/>Note the implementation guidance for the domain where this template is used should be consulted regarding correct usage of the originalText element.  </text>
                    </otherAnnotation>
                </annotations>
                <derivationSupplier attributeName="code" className="Act" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
                <type name="CV"/>
                <supplierDomainSpecification codingStrength="CNE" domainName="CarePlanComponentType"/>
            </attribute>
            <attribute isMandatory="false" maximumMultiplicity="1"
                minimumMultiplicity="0" name="effectiveTime" sortKey="0">
                <annotations>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>The time of the Care Plan component.<br/>
                            <br/>The date range shall be carried as follows:<br/>
                            <br/>If a single point in time is to be carried the Date or Time Point data type shall be used:<br/>
                            <br/>
                            <ul>
                                <li>The center attribute shall contain the date.</li>
                            </ul>
                            <br/>This datatype is used if date of the care plan is not fully known / available<br/>
                            <br/>If both a start date and an end date are present the Date or Time Interval Complete data type shall be used:<br/>
                            <br/>
                            <ul>
                                <li>The low attribute shall contain the start date.</li>
                                <li>The high attribute shall contain the end date.</li>
                            </ul>
                            <br/>If only a start date is present the Date or Time Interval After data type shall be used:<br/>
                            <br/>
                            <ul>
                                <li>The low attribute shall contain the start date.</li>
                            </ul>
                            <br type="_moz"/>
                        </text>
                    </otherAnnotation>
                </annotations>
                <derivationSupplier attributeName="effectiveTime"
                    className="Act" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
                <type name="IVL">
                    <supplierBindingArgumentDatatype name="TS"/>
                </type>
            </attribute>
        </class>
    </ownedClass>
