                    </graphicRepresentation>
                </constraint>
                <otherAnnotation type="html">
                    <text>
                        <div>
                            <p>
                                <b>Refers to a performer of the Care Plan component.</b>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <b>Where performer participation is used, then all performers must be stated,  even if they authored the act.</b>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <b>
                                    <br/>
                                </b>
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </text>
                </otherAnnotation>
            </annotations>
            <attribute conformance="R" isMandatory="true"
                maximumMultiplicity="1" minimumMultiplicity="1"
                name="contentId" sortKey="0">
                <annotations>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>
                            <div>
                                <p>This attribute, when valued in an instance, provides a unique forward pointing identifier for a template which constrains the classes and attributes which follow. </p>
                                <p>The attribute is intended simply as a structural navigational aid and should not be relied upon as an indicator of semantic meaning.</p>
                                <p>The IdentifierExternal datatype flavour is used to carry this information as follows:</p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>The root attribute shall contain the OID "2.16.840.1.113883.2.1.3.2.4.18.16"</li>
                                    <li>The extension attribute shall contain the template artifact Id.</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </text>
                    </otherAnnotation>
                </annotations>
                <derivationSupplier attributeName="contentId"
                    className="Participation" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
                <type name="II"/>
            </attribute>
            <attribute conformance="R"
                defaultValue="COCD_TP146076UK02#performer"
                fixedValue="COCD_TP146076UK02#performer"
                isMandatory="true" maximumMultiplicity="1"
                minimumMultiplicity="1" name="templateId" sortKey="0">
                <annotations>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>
                            <div>
                                <p>The fixed value of this attribute provides a unique identifier for the  template and the classname within that template.</p>
                                <p>The IdentifierExternal datatype flavour is used to carry this information as follows:</p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>The root attribute shall contain the OID "2.16.840.1.113883.2.1.3.2.4.18.2"</li>
                                    <li>The extension attribute shall contain the fixed value.</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </text>
                    </otherAnnotation>
                </annotations>
                <derivationSupplier attributeName="templateId"
                    className="Participation" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
                <type name="II"/>
            </attribute>
            <attribute conformance="R" fixedValue="PRF"
                isMandatory="true" isStructural="true"
                maximumMultiplicity="1" minimumMultiplicity="1"
                name="typeCode" sortKey="1">
                <annotations>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>
                            <p>Indicates that this is a performer.</p>
                        </text>
                    </otherAnnotation>
                </annotations>
                <derivationSupplier attributeName="typeCode"
                    className="Participation" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
                <type name="CS"/>
                <supplierDomainSpecification codingStrength="CNE" domainName="PRF"/>
            </attribute>
            <attribute conformance="R" defaultValue="OP" fixedValue="OP"
                isMandatory="true" isStructural="true"
                maximumMultiplicity="1" minimumMultiplicity="1"
                name="contextControlCode" sortKey="3">
                <annotations>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>
                            <p>Specifies how the performer contributes to the context of the Care Plan act and whether they / it may be propagated to descendent acts whose association allows such propagation. </p>
                            <p>"O" (Overriding)- the association replaces any context of the same or more specific type that has been conducted from the parent act. </p>"P" (Propagating)- the association is conducted to all child acts where the ActRelationship.contextConductionInd is set to "true." </text>
                    </otherAnnotation>
                </annotations>
                <derivationSupplier attributeName="contextControlCode"
                    className="Participation" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
                <type name="CS"/>
                <supplierDomainSpecification codingStrength="CNE" domainName="ContextControl"/>
            </attribute>
            <attribute isMandatory="false" maximumMultiplicity="1"
                minimumMultiplicity="0" name="time" sortKey="7">
                <annotations>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>
                            <div>
                                <p>The time that the performer is / was required to perform the Care Plan component. <br/>
                                </p>
                                <p>The date range shall be carried as follows: </p>
                                <p>If a single point in time is to be carried the Date or Time Point data type  shall be used: </p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>The <i>center </i>attribute shall contain the date.</li>
                                </ul>This datatype is used if date of the care event is not fully known /  available<br/>
                                <p/>
                                <p>If both a start date and an end date are present the Date or Time Interval  Complete data type shall be used: </p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>The <i>low</i> attribute shall contain the start date.  </li>
                                    <li>The <i>high</i> attribute shall contain the end date. </li>
                                </ul>
                                <p>If only a start date is present the Date or Time Interval After data type  shall be used: </p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>The <i>low</i> attribute shall contain the start date.</li>
                                </ul>                                 This datatype would only be used if the Care Plan component is still ongoing.<br/>
                            </div>
                        </text>
                    </otherAnnotation>
                </annotations>
                <derivationSupplier attributeName="time"
                    className="Participation" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
                <type name="IVL">
                    <supplierBindingArgumentDatatype name="TS"/>
                </type>
            </attribute>
            <attribute isMandatory="false" maximumMultiplicity="1"
                minimumMultiplicity="0" name="modeCode" sortKey="8">
                <annotations>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>
                            <div>
                                <p>The mode in which the performer will / did perform the Care Plan.</p>
                                <p>The Coded Only datatype flavour is used to carry this information as  follows:</p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>The <i>code</i> attribute will contain a value from the list of codes in  the ParticipationMode vocabulary</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </text>
                    </otherAnnotation>
                </annotations>
                <derivationSupplier attributeName="modeCode"
                    className="Participation" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
                <type name="CS"/>
                <supplierDomainSpecification codingStrength="CNE" domainName="ParticipationMode"/>
            </attribute>
        </class>
    </ownedClass>
